Perfect! Since your project is working locally, here's the deployment process I recommend:

Frontend: React + Vite → Vercel
Backend: Spring Boot + Spring AI + Groq → Render
Source Code: GitHub

This is free and looks professional on your resume.

Phase 1: Push Your Code to GitHub
1. Create a GitHub Repository

Name it:

PrajwalGPT

Description:

Enterprise AI Assistant built with Spring Boot, Spring AI, Groq, React & Tailwind CSS.

Keep it Public.

2. Push Your Code

Backend:

git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/<YOUR_USERNAME>/PrajwalGPT.git
git push -u origin main

If your frontend is a separate project, create another repository (for example, PrajwalGPT-Frontend) or keep both in a monorepo with backend/ and frontend/ folders.

Phase 2: Deploy Spring Boot on Render
1. Go to Render

https://render.com

Login with GitHub.

2. Click
New

↓

Web Service
3. Select your GitHub repository

Choose the repository containing the Spring Boot application.

4. Configure

Name

prajwalgpt-api

Language

Java

Branch

main

Root Directory

Leave empty if the backend is at the repository root. If it's inside a backend folder, set it to:

backend

Build Command

./mvnw clean package

If you don't have the Maven Wrapper, use:

mvn clean package

Start Command

java -jar target/*.jar
5. Environment Variables

Add these in Render:

Key	Value
SPRING_AI_OPENAI_API_KEY	Your Groq API key
SPRING_AI_OPENAI_BASE_URL	https://api.groq.com/openai/v1
SPRING_AI_OPENAI_CHAT_MODEL	llama-3.3-70b-versatile

Then update application.properties:

spring.ai.openai.api-key=${SPRING_AI_OPENAI_API_KEY}
spring.ai.openai.base-url=${SPRING_AI_OPENAI_BASE_URL}
spring.ai.openai.chat.model=${SPRING_AI_OPENAI_CHAT_MODEL}

Commit and push these changes (without hardcoding your API key).

6. Deploy

Render will build your application.

You'll get a URL similar to:

https://prajwalgpt-api.onrender.com

Test it:

https://prajwalgpt-api.onrender.com/api/default/hello
Phase 3: Deploy React on Vercel

Go to:

https://vercel.com

Sign in with GitHub.

Click:

Add New Project

Import your React repository.

Environment Variable

In Vercel, add:

Key	Value
VITE_API_URL	https://prajwalgpt-api.onrender.com/api
Update api.js
import axios from "axios";

const api = axios.create({
  baseURL: import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL,
});

export default api;

export async function askAI(conversationId, message) {
  const response = await api.get(
    `/${conversationId}/${encodeURIComponent(message)}`
  );
  return response.data;
}
Deploy

Vercel will provide a URL like:

https://prajwalgpt.vercel.app
Phase 4: Update Backend CORS

Allow your Vercel domain:

configuration.setAllowedOrigins(List.of(
    "http://localhost:5173",
    "https://prajwalgpt.vercel.app"
));

If your Vercel URL changes while testing, update it accordingly.

Phase 5: Test

Open your deployed frontend:

https://prajwalgpt.vercel.app

Ask:

Hello

If everything is configured correctly, you'll receive a response from Groq through your deployed Spring Boot backend.

